================================================================================
                            WHAT IS PERMITTED
================================================================================

✅ ALLOWED USES:

1. INTERNAL USE
   Using TopGun within your organization for any internal purpose.

2. APPLICATION BACKEND
   Embedding TopGun as part of your application's data layer, where TopGun
   is not directly exposed as a database service to your customers.

3. DEVELOPMENT & TESTING
   Using TopGun for development, testing, evaluation, and non-production
   purposes without any restrictions.

4. SELF-HOSTED DEPLOYMENT
   Deploying TopGun on your own infrastructure for your own applications.

5. CONSULTING & PROFESSIONAL SERVICES
   Providing consulting, integration, and professional services around TopGun.

6. EDUCATIONAL USE
   Using TopGun for learning, teaching, research, and educational purposes.

7. OPEN SOURCE PROJECTS
   Using TopGun in open source projects (as long as those projects don't
   offer TopGun as a managed database service).

================================================================================
                           WHAT IS NOT PERMITTED
================================================================================

❌ PROHIBITED WITHOUT A COMMERCIAL LICENSE:

1. MANAGED DATABASE SERVICE
   Offering TopGun to third parties as a commercial hosted database service,
   database-as-a-service (DBaaS), or managed database offering.

   Examples of prohibited use:
   - "TopGun Cloud" - a hosted TopGun service
   - Multi-tenant database platform built on TopGun
   - Reselling TopGun hosting as a primary business

================================================================================
                             CHANGE LICENSE
================================================================================

Each version of TopGun will automatically convert to the Apache License 2.0
four (4) years after its release date.

This means:
- Version released on January 1, 2025 → Apache 2.0 on January 1, 2029
- You can use older versions under Apache 2.0 once they pass the Change Date

================================================================================
                          COMMERCIAL LICENSING
================================================================================

If your intended use falls outside the Additional Use Grant (e.g., you want
to offer TopGun as a managed database service), please contact us for
commercial licensing options.

